snippet: An administrative court determined that the election’s May 23 starting date had been wrongly set, but legal experts said the ruling was expected to have little effect.
abstract: Administrative court in Cairo suspends Egypt’s upcoming presidential election due to a procedural issue; Egyptians express disbelief and derision over the ruling, which underscores the lack of certainty over many details, but legal experts say that they expect the election to proceed as scheduled.
lead_paragraph: An administrative court determined that the election’s May 23 starting date had been wrongly set, but legal experts said the ruling was expected to have little effect.

headline.seo: Egypt Presidential Election Is Suspended by Court
